tumatakuru
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:  1
Definition:[Ma.] a prickly native shrub Discaria toumatou [commonly corrupted from the Maori tumatakuru to matagouri.]


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See: matagouri
Pronunciation:
Notes: tumatagora, tumatikura, tomatagaru, toumatakuru, tomatagorra, tumatagowry
