Date:  0/0/1898
Source:  Austral English
Author:  MORRIS
Vol / Page:  482
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Tumata-kuru, n.</i> Maori name for plant better known as <i>Wild Irishman</i> (q.v.), <i>Discaria toumatou,</i> Raoul. `A thorny plant, very difficult to handle.' (Vincent Pyke.) <i>Tumatagowry</i>, or <i>Matagory </i>(q.v.), is the Southern corruption of contractors, labourers, and others.
Notes:

Date:  0/0/1898
Source:  Merriam-Webster Third International
Author:
Vol / Page:  2033
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Tu&#769;.ma&#769;.tu-ku&#769;.ru</i> (tu&#769;.ma.&#769;.tu-ku&#769;.ru),<i> n</i>. [Maori.] [Written also <i>tomatakuru.] (Bot.) </i>A New Zealand tree (<i>Discaria toumatou</i>) of the order <i>Rhamneae</i>; - called also <i>matagory</i> and <i>wild Irishman.</i>
